critical_positive: I think that we were both open to talking with a stranger and we found we had a fair bit in common. We are at different stages in our lives and have different political perspectives but all in all I think we approach the world in a similar light. Other than that, it came down to us both being friendly and open.
critical_negative: We failed to do the classic small talk and never introduced ourselves, even at the end after an hour of talking. We hopped around from topic to topic a bit haphazardly. I also feel I could have let her talk more rather than dominating some parts of the conversation. This is not the first time I have had this issue, to say the least.

begin_memory_text: During the beginning of the conversation, we were talking about what we do for work, and what kind of side jobs we do for extra income.
middle_memory_text: In the middle of the conversation, we were talking about politics and how things are currently affecting the environment nation wide (the wildfires, capitalism, immigration, etc.).
end_memory_text: Towards the end of the conversation, we were talking about things we can do to prepare in case of a crisis.  Some of the things we covered were farming, food storage, and cooking.
rest_of_day_open: I think some of this week will be interesting to say the least, but overall I can see it going pretty good.  I'm not directly involved, but there is an upcoming court case that I know is going to be a bit stressful this week, so hopefully things go well in our favor.  I can't see anything else going wrong this week otherwise.
critical_positive: I think what made the conversation work really well was how passionate we were about similar topics.  While our exact beliefs differ a little here and there, they were overall striving for the same peace towards our nation.  It was interesting getting to hear some about each other's lives too, as we dove deeper into the conversation.
critical_negative: There wasn't anything that didn't work out in the conversation we just had.  I feel like the conversation flowed smoothly.  There weren't any mass disagreements or awkward pauses or anything of that sort.  Unfortunately I had to cut the conversation short because I had to get back to helping my sister out with her baby (and by short I mean we were talking for an hour), but otherwise the conversation was great!
